\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs54\i\f1 Reader:}{ }{\cs53\f1\fs32 O Lord my God, in Thee have I put my hope; save me from them that persecute me, and do Thou deliver me. 
\par Lest at any time like a lion he seize my soul, when there is none to redeem me, nor to save. 
\par O Lord, my God, if I have done this, if there be injustice in my hands, 
\par If I have paid back evil to them that rendered evil unto me, then let me fall back empty from mine enemies. 
\par Then let the enemy pursue my soul, and take it, and let him tread down my life into the earth, and my glory let him bring down into the dust. 
\par Arise, O Lord, in Thine anger, exalt Thyself to the furthest boundaries of Thine enemies. 
\par And arouse Thyself, O Lord my God, in the commandment which Thou hast enjoined, and a congregation of peoples shall surround Thee. And for their sakes return Thou on high. 
\par The Lord shall judge the peoples. Judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to mine innocence within me. 
\par Let the wickedness of sinners be ended, and do Thou guide the righteous man, O God, that searchest out the hearts and reins. 
\par Righteous is my help from God, Who saveth them who are upright of heart. 
\par God is a judge that is righteous, strong and forbearing, and inflicteth not wrath every day. 
\par Unless ye be converted, His glittering sword shall He furbish; He hath bent His bow, and hath made it ready. 
\par And on it He hath made ready the instruments of death, His arrows for them that rage hotly hath He perfected. 
\par Behold, he was in travail with unrighteousness, he hath conceived toil and brought forth iniquity. 
\par He opened a pit and dug it, and he shall fall into the hole which he hath made. 
\par His toil shall return upon his own head, and upon his own pate shall his unrighteousness come down. 
\par I will give praise unto the Lord according to His righteousness, and I will chant unto the name of the Lord Most High. 
\par }\pard\plain \s55\qc\widctlpar\adjustright \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\cgrid {\cs44\i0  PSALM 8 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs53\f1\fs32 O Lord, our Lord, how wonderful is Thy name in all the earth! For Thy magnificence is lifted high above the heavens. 
\par Out of the mouths of babes and sucklings hast Thou perfected praise, because of Thine enemies, to destroy the enemy and avenger. 
\par For I will behold the heavens, the works of Thy fingers, the moon and the stars, which Thou hast founded. 
\par What is man, that Thou art mindful of him? Or the son of man, that Thou visitest him? 
\par Thou hast made him a little lower than the angels; with glory and honour hast Thou crowned him, and Thou hast set him over the works of Thy hands. 
\par All things hast Thou subjected under his feet, sheep, and all oxen, yea, and the beasts of the field, 
\par The birds of the air, and the fish of the sea, the things that pass through the paths of the sea. 
\par O Lord, our Lord, how wonderful is Thy name in all the earth! 
\par  Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par  Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par  Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par  Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God.
