And the deacon chanteth the prokeimenon. The choir then
 repeats the prokeimenon, and the deacon chants each verse in order, after which the choir repeats the prokeimenon. At the end the deacon chanteth the first half of the prokeimenon, and the choir finishes}{. 
\par }\pard \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs40 THE DAILY PROKIMENA}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Saturday evening, the Sixth Tone:
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 The Lord is King, He is clothed with majesty.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Stichos 1:}{\cs47\b\fs36  The Lord is clothed with strength and He hath girt Himself}{.
\par }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Stichos 2:}{\cs47\b\fs36  For He established the world which shall not be shaken.}{
\par  }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Stichos 3:}{\cs47\b\fs36  Holiness becometh Thy house, O Lord, unto length of days.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Sunday evening, the Eighth Tone:}{ 
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 Behold now, bless ye the Lord, all ye servants of the Lord.}{
\par }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Stichos:}{\cs47\b\fs36  Ye that stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Monday evening, the Fourth Tone:}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 The Lord will hearken unto me when I cry unto Him.}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36  Stichos: When I called upon Thee, O God of my righteousness, Thou didst hearken unto me.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Tuesday evening, the First Tone:}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 Thy mercy, O Lord, shall pursue me all the days of my life.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Stichos}{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 :}{\cs47\b\fs36  The Lord is my shepherd, and I shall not want. In a place of green pasture, there hath He made me to dwell.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Wednesday evening, the Fifth Tone:}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 O God, in Thy name save me, and in Thy strength do Thou judge me.}{
\par }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Stichos:}{\cs47\b\fs36  O God, hearken unto my prayer, give ear unto the words of my mouth.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Thursday evening, the Sixth Tone:}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 My help cometh from the Lord, Who hath made heaven and the earth.}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 Stichos: I have lifted up mine eyes to the Mountains, from whence cometh my help.}{
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 On Friday evening, the Seventh Tone:}{
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 O God, my helper art Thou, and Thy mercy shall go before me.}{
\par }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Stichos:}{\cs47\b\fs36  Rescue me from mine enemies, O God, and from them that rise up against me redeem me.
