\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 If there be a Litia, the sichera are sung here. As they are chanted. The priest and decon proceed through the North door of 
the altar to the middle of the church, in front of a standing candle. They make three bows, and then the deacon taketh the censer and doeth a small censing (the iconastasis, clergy, people) After the last sticheron, the deacon saith: 
