\par Then we sing the Aposticha. If it is a Saturday evening, we sing the Aposticha of the Resurrection, with these stichoi:}{\b\i Stichos 1}{: The Lord is King, * He is clothed with majesty.
\par }{\b\i Stichos 2:}{ }{\cs53\f1\fs32 For He established the world}{ * which shall not be shaken.
\par }{\b\i Stichos 3:}{ }{\cs53\f1\fs32 Holiness becometh Thy house, O Lord,}{ * unto length of days.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 If there is a polyeleos (other than Saturday evening), we sing the Aposticha of the saint from the Menaion, with its stichoi. If the service is a great feast of the Lord, we
 sing the Aposticha appointed for the feast with its stichoi, no matter what day it falls on.
\par Then, after the Aposticha, the prayer of St. Symeon:}{
