\par }{\cs59\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15 Choir:}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 God is the Lord and hath appeared unto us. Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord.}{ }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 This is sung after each stichos.
\par }{\cs47\b\fs36 Stichos 2: Surrounding me they compassed me, and by the name of the Lord I warded them off.
\par Stichos 3: I shall not die, but live, and I shall tell of the works of the Lord.
\par }{ }{\cs47\b\fs36 Stichos 4: The stone which the builders rejected, the same is become the head of the corner. This is the Lord\rquote s doing, and it is marvelous in our eyes.
\par }{\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\cf6 The Sunday (Resurrectional) Troparia of the Eight Tones:
\par }\pard \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 1:}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 When the stone had been sealed by the Jews,* And the soldiers were guarding Thine immaculate Body,* Thou didst arise on the third day, O Savior, * granting 
life unto the world. * Wherefore, the Hosts of the Heavens cried out to Thee, O Life-giver: * Glory to Thy resurrection, O Christ. * Glory to Thy kingdom. * Glory to Thy dispensation, O only Lover of mankind.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 2}{: }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 When Thou didst descend unto death, O 
Life Immortal, * then didst Thou slay Hades with the lightning of Thy Divinity. * And when Thou didst also raise the dead out of the nethermost depths, * all the Hosts of the heavens cried out: * O Life-giver, Christ our God, glory be to Thee.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 3:}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 Let the heavens be glad; let earthly things rejoice; * for the Lord hath wrought might with His arm. * He hath trampled down death by death; * the first-born of the dead hath He become. * 
From the belly of Hades hath He delivered us * and Hath granted to the world great mercy.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 4:}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 
Having learned the joyful proclamation of the Resurrection from the angel, * and having cast off the ancestral condemnation, * the women disciples of the Lord spake to the apostles exultantly: * Death is despoiled and Christ Go
d is risen, * granting to the world great mercy.
\par }{ }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 5}{\cs60\i\f1\fs36\cf15 :}{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15  
Let us, O faithful, praise and worship the Word * Who is co-unoriginate with the Father and the Spirit, * and Who was born of the Virgin for our salvation; * for He was pleased to ascend the Cross 
in the flesh * and to endure death, * and to raise the dead by His glorious Resurrection.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 6.}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 Angelic hosts were above Thy tomb, * and they that guarded Thee became as dead. And Mary stood by the grave seeking Thine immaculate body. * Thou didst despo
il hades and wast not tempted by it. * Thou didst meet the Virgin and didst grant us life. * O Thou Who didst rise from the dead, O Lord, glory be to Thee.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 7.}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 Thou didst destroy death by Thy Cross, * Thou didst open paradise to the thief. * Thou dids
t change the lamentation of the Myrrh-bearers, * and Thou didst command Thine Apostles to proclaim * that Thou didst arise, O Christ God, * and grantest to the world great mercy.
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 Tone 8:}{ }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 From on high didst Thou descend, O compassionate One; * to burial of three days hast Thou submitted * that Thou mightest free us from our passions. * O our Life and Resurrection, O Lord, glory be to Thee.

