\par On Sundays, when there is always a minimum of 8 stichera appointed (unless it is a great feast of the Lord) these two stichoi are added (when all the stichera are from the
\par Octoechos, otherwise we use two psalm verses for saint or feast of the day, usually taken from the verses at the aposticha in the menaion):
\par  
\par }{\cs53\f1\fs32 Arise, O Lord my God, let Thy hands be lifted high;}{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15  * forget not Thy paupers to the end.}{ Sticheron.
\par }{\cs53\f1\fs32 I will confess Thee, O Lord, with my whole heart,}{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15  * I will tell of all Thy wonders.}{ Sticheron.
