\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Tone 1: }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 Today is salvation come unto the world; * let us sing praises to Him that arose from the tome, * and is the Author of our life. * For, having 
destroyed death by death, * He hath given us the victory and great mercy.
\par }\pard \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright { 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 If is a 2nd, 4th, 6th, or 8th Tone Sunday, we sing:
\par }{ 
\par Tone 2: }{\cs60\f1\fs36\cf15 Having risen from the tomb, and having burst the bonds of hades, * Thou hast destroyed the sentence of death, O Lord, * delivering all from the
\par snares of the enemy. * Manifesting Thyself to Thine apostles, Thou didst send them forth to preach; * and through them hast granted Thy peace to the world, * O
\par Thou Who alone art plenteous in mercy.
\par }{
